Source: oxen-libquic
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jason Rhinelander <jason@oxen.io>
Build-Depends:
    debhelper-compat (= 13),
    cmake (>= 3.18),
    g++,
    pkg-config,
    libngtcp2-dev (>= 1.1.0~),
    libngtcp2-crypto-gnutls-dev (>= 1.1.0~),
    libgnutls28-dev (>= 3.7.2),
    libevent-dev,
    liboxenc-dev (>= 1.0.10)
Standards-Version: 4.4.1
Section: libs
Homepage: https://github.com/oxen-io/oxen-libquic

Package: liboxen-quic-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: liboxen-quic@LIB_VERSION@ (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}, libgnutls28-dev (>= 3.7.2), libevent-dev, liboxenc-dev (>= 1.0.10)
Description: C++ library for multi-stream QUIC implementations (headers)
 This C++17 library builds upon ngtcp2 to provide a C++ interface to making and
 accepting QUIC connections.
 .
 This package contains the library headers and other development files needed
 to build software using libquic.

Package: liboxen-quic@LIB_VERSION@
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: C++ library for multi-stream QUIC implementations
 This C++17 library builds upon ngtcp2 to provide a C++ interface to making and
 accepting QUIC connections.
 .
 This package contains the library file needed by software built using
 oxen-libquic.

Package: oxen-quic-tools
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: C++ library for multi-stream QUIC implementations
 This C++17 library builds upon ngtcp2 to provide a C++ interface to making and
 accepting QUIC connections.
 .
 This package contains the speedtest binaries used for testing QUIC performance.
